cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CC

This paper is about Word Sense Disambiguation (WSD), which is a subfield of Natural Language Processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses various supervised learning algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of these algorithms, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
